вЂЄ-[Sarah] Dad.
вЂЄ-Yes.

206
00:10:38.333 --> 00:10:41.708
вЂЄI-I thought you'd call
вЂЄor at least reschedule our meeting

207
00:10:41.791 --> 00:10:43.875
вЂЄ-since you stood me up.
вЂЄ-W-What are you talking about?

208
00:10:43.958 --> 00:10:45.875
вЂЄOur lunch date. Dad.

209
00:10:45.958 --> 00:10:48.916
вЂЄBuhle scheduled it for us
вЂЄand you said you'd be there.

210
00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:50.500
вЂЄbut you never even showed up.

211
00:10:50.583 --> 00:10:51.916
вЂЄOkay. okay.

212
00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:53.916
вЂЄBuhle must've mixed the dates.

213
00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:56.208
вЂЄOh. okay. So when can we meet?

214
00:10:56.291 --> 00:10:57.708
вЂЄI'll let you know.

215
00:10:57.791 --> 00:10:58.875
вЂЄ[scoffs]

216
00:11:02.958 --> 00:11:04.583
вЂЄDad. what happened to our picture?

217
00:11:05.541 --> 00:11:06.958
вЂЄ[stammers] What?

218
00:11:07.041 --> 00:11:09.291
вЂЄDo I have to explain everything
вЂЄthat happens in this office?

219
00:11:09.375 --> 00:11:11.916
вЂЄ-Yes. that's our family photo that I--
вЂЄ-For crying out loud!

220
00:11:12.583 --> 00:11:15.250
вЂЄStop it. this is my office. Listen here.

221
00:11:15.333 --> 00:11:17.833
вЂЄThere are many girls
вЂЄwho would kill to have what you have.

222
00:11:17.916 --> 00:11:20.583
вЂЄYou have everything you could want.
вЂЄYet here you are.

223
00:11:20.666 --> 00:11:23.583
вЂЄThe world does not revolve around you.

224
00:11:23.666 --> 00:11:26.833
вЂЄYou need to stop with this behaviour.
вЂЄYou understand me?

225
00:11:27.458 --> 00:11:28.708
вЂЄStop it!

226
00:11:39.666 --> 00:11:40.833
вЂЄ[sighs]

227
00:11:45.833 --> 00:11:46.916
вЂЄ[door opens]

228
00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:51.416
вЂЄ-[door closes]
вЂЄ-[footsteps approaching]

229
00:11:53.291 --> 00:11:54.291
вЂЄ[doctor clears throat]

230
00:11:55.375 --> 00:11:56.375
вЂЄ[sighs]

231
00:11:56.458 --> 00:11:59.250
вЂЄSo. um. is it cervical cancer?

232
00:11:59.750 --> 00:12:02.541
вЂЄUh. the pap smear results
вЂЄare not back yet. ma'am.

233
00:12:03.666 --> 00:12:05.166
вЂЄBut there is something else.

234
00:12:05.916 --> 00:12:07.333
вЂЄ[stutters] Something else?

235
00:12:07.916 --> 00:12:09.791
вЂЄThe tests show that

236
00:12:11.250 --> 00:12:12.458
вЂЄyou have gonorrhoea.

237
00:12:12.541 --> 00:12:14.291
вЂЄ[suspenseful music playing]

238
00:12:14.375 --> 00:12:15.375
вЂЄ[gasps]

239
00:12:16.500 --> 00:12:18.250
вЂЄ[stammers] I'm sorry. the STI?

240
00:12:18.333 --> 00:12:20.333
вЂЄSo. ma'am. unlike men.

241
00:12:20.416 --> 00:12:23.958
вЂЄthe symptoms in women
вЂЄmay be too subtle to identify.

242
00:12:25.708 --> 00:12:26.958
вЂЄO-Okay.

243
00:12:28.625 --> 00:12:31.333
вЂЄ[sighs] So you're saying my partner

244
00:12:32.166 --> 00:12:33.500
вЂЄcould've been having the symptoms?

245
00:12:33.583 --> 00:12:37.000
вЂЄHe probably thinks
вЂЄit's something that will just go away.

246
00:12:37.666 --> 00:12:42.458
вЂЄBut we are able to treat it with
вЂЄthe antibiotics I've prescribed for you.

247
00:12:43.291 --> 00:12:46.916
вЂЄBut please.
вЂЄhe also has to come in for treatment.

248
00:12:53.458 --> 00:12:56.583
вЂЄ[Essie] Freedom. please. please
вЂЄpour a glass of wine for your sister.

249
00:12:56.666 --> 00:12:58.500
вЂЄMaybe it'll calm her down.

250
00:12:58.583 --> 00:13:00.000
вЂЄIt'll help her reduce stress.

251
00:13:00.083 --> 00:13:02.666
вЂЄ-She's been crying the whole day.
вЂЄ-Why don't we give her whiskey?

252
00:13:02.750 --> 00:13:05.250
вЂЄ-Maybe that'll make her feel better?
вЂЄ-[Essie] I'm not joking.

253
00:13:06.791 --> 00:13:09.916
вЂЄI mean. she's been crying for hours.
вЂЄShe's burning up now.

254
00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:12.333
вЂЄ-Her head must be pounding.
вЂЄ-Ma. I'm not going to do that.

255
00:13:12.875 --> 00:13:15.416
вЂЄ-Sarah doesn't need alcohol to cope.
вЂЄ-[Sarah] Mom.

256
00:13:16.083 --> 00:13:17.500
вЂЄI don't want alcohol.

257
00:13:19.041 --> 00:13:20.083
вЂЄOh.

258
00:13:21.875 --> 00:13:23.083
вЂЄOkay. then. my baby.

259
00:13:23.166 --> 00:13:28.583
вЂЄSo how about me and you go to the mall
вЂЄand get you some new clothes?

260
00:13:28.666 --> 00:13:30.458
вЂЄ-You'll look beautiful and you--
вЂЄ-[Sarah scoffs]

261
00:13:30.541 --> 00:13:33.083
вЂЄYou know what? I want to be alone. Ma.

262
00:13:33.708 --> 00:13:35.791
вЂЄOh. Did I say something wrong?

263
00:13:35.875 --> 00:13:36.958
вЂЄSarah!

264
00:13:37.916 --> 00:13:39.166
вЂЄSarah. come back.

265
00:13:40.791 --> 00:13:43.416
вЂЄ-[sighs] This is all Jonasi's fault.
вЂЄ-[door slams]

266
00:13:45.250 --> 00:13:46.541
вЂЄThis is all your fault.

267
00:13:50.291 --> 00:13:52.625
вЂЄMa. you chose to love Jonasi
вЂЄover your own kids.

268
00:13:52.708 --> 00:13:55.750
вЂЄ-That's not true.
вЂЄ-Your love for money and men

269
00:13:55.833 --> 00:13:58.041
вЂЄhas left you with wounded kids.

270
00:13:58.125 --> 00:14:02.291
вЂЄBut of course you can't see anymore
вЂЄthat in here. our hearts have been broken.

271
00:14:02.375 --> 00:14:04.166
вЂЄYour excessive drinking is your problem.

272
00:14:04.250 --> 00:14:05.916
вЂЄDon't blame me for your addiction.

273
00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:08.666
вЂЄ-You chose this life.
вЂЄ-You know what? This is madness now.

274
00:14:08.750 --> 00:14:11.125
вЂЄOld lady. this is all your fault.

275
00:14:11.875 --> 00:14:15.375
вЂЄYou allowed that dog.
вЂЄJonasi. to come into our home. old lady.

276
00:14:16.708 --> 00:14:19.416
вЂЄAnd he treated me
вЂЄlike an animal who eats trash.

277
00:14:19.500 --> 00:14:21.041
вЂЄsomething worthless. all the way through.

278
00:14:21.125 --> 00:14:22.458
вЂЄ[emotional music playing]

279
00:14:23.500 --> 00:14:24.708
вЂЄAnd you just watched.

280
00:14:25.875 --> 00:14:30.375
вЂЄI've always known my whole life
вЂЄthat you don't really care about me.

281
00:14:30.458 --> 00:14:33.083
вЂЄThe only thing you really care about is

282
00:14:33.625 --> 00:14:36.083
вЂЄ-money.
вЂЄ-I'm not with Jonasi because of money.

283
00:14:36.166 --> 00:14:38.791
вЂЄ-[scoffs]
вЂЄ-I've been with Jonasi for a long time.

284
00:14:38.875 --> 00:14:40.208
вЂЄBefore you were even born.

285
00:14:40.291 --> 00:14:43.083
вЂЄ-[laughs]
вЂЄ-Wow.

286
00:14:43.166 --> 00:14:44.541
вЂЄYou know. my old lady.

287
00:14:45.916 --> 00:14:47.750
вЂЄThis is not funny at all.

288
00:14:49.208 --> 00:14:51.125
вЂЄSo tell me then. old lady.

289
00:14:52.125 --> 00:14:53.208
вЂЄHmm?

290
00:14:53.291 --> 00:14:55.916
вЂЄIf you didn't love Jonasi
вЂЄjust because of his money.

291
00:14:56.625 --> 00:14:58.208
